      "summary": "International Aid Charity (IAC) is a humanitarian organization dedicated to providing emergency relief, education, and orphan sponsorship to marginalized communities, primarily in <cite id=\"1\">Jordan and other crisis-affected regions</cite>. The organization has demonstrated remarkable growth, achieving a <cite id=\"2\">3-year revenue CAGR of 69.7%</cite>, with total revenue reaching <cite id=\"3\">$1,481,959 in the 2023 tax year</cite>. IAC maintains a strong commitment to financial efficiency, reporting a <cite id=\"4\">program expense ratio of 87.8%</cite> according to its most recent filing, though Charity Navigator identifies a <cite id=\"5\">program expense ratio of 87.8%</cite> when adjusting for specific functional allocations. The charity is particularly distinguished by its <cite id=\"6\">fundraising efficiency of $0.00 per $1 raised</cite>, ensuring that public donations are not eroded by high solicitation costs. Beyond immediate relief, IAC operates <cite id=\"7\">refugee schools and youth soccer programs</cite> to provide holistic support to displaced populations. Their operations are <cite id=\"8\">verified as zakat-eligible</cite>, serving specific asnaf categories including the poor (fuqara) and needy (masakin).",
